<user_id>102011885661472804637< /user_id><rate>5< /rate><user_name>Chad Orcutt<//user_name><Date>1557161804271< /Date>< review>
I lost my upper teeth in an accident in my 30‚Äôs and it was truly one of the worst things I‚Äôve been through. I had a bad experience a few years back and I was worried that implants were just not going to be an option for me. I was convinced that I would just wear a denture for the rest of my life. I met Dr. Smith after seeing an ad on TV. She took care to ensure that I was a good candidate then explained the process to me thoroughly before I made my decision. The staff helped me figure out the best treatment plan for me based on my needs and my wallet.

A full replacement of my upper teeth was more expensive than I really wanted to pay but once I compared the cost of mini implants to regular implants, I was convinced it was worth it. I decided on the nicest material because I really wanted them to look natural and stay with me for a long time.

The process wasn‚Äôt perfectly easy, there was some problems with my temporary bite and it caused some extra visits. My temporary broke on Christmas Eve and I called the answering service. Someone met me at the office within 30 minutes and spent hours fixing my temporary and ensuring that I could eat Christmas dinner with my family. It was a huge deal to me. I chose sedation for the initial procedure and it was way easier than I thought it would be. Pain was minimal after the procedure was done on Saturday I was back at work on Monday.

After about 6 weeks from the start I have the kind of teeth that people notice and make comments about. Teeth that I can actually eat with. I am so proud of my new smile and I actually open my mouth to talk.

Anyone can write a review about their dentist but Its impossible for me to express exactly what this process has done for me and how well I have been treated by everyone at Dr.  Smith‚Äôs office. I still get emotional just thinking about where I started and where I am now after just a couple of months.

I know this is your business but my wife and I will never forget what you have done for us.

Chad and Erinn Orcutt</review>

<Rating>5<//Rating>< Review>
I live in the Bay Area and I travel to Sacramento to see Dr. Smith. I have been her patient for over 11 years and no matter where I live in California, I make the trip to see Dr. Smith. Family n friends all think I'm crazy and try to recommend other dentists but none of them live up to Dr. Smith.

I have a severe phobia of dentists, struggle with anxiety and have a panic attack disorder. Dr. Smith's sedation services make dentistry possible for me despite my limitations. Other sedation dentists want to use IV sedation but Dr. Smith only uses the most minimally evasive options in all her work, including sedation. I know I'm a difficult patient but Dr. Smith makes me feel like her favorite patient and I am so grateful to have a dentist like her.

I tell her all the time, "If it wasn't for you, I would have no teeth." She smiles n laughs but it's true! No matter what it is that's keeping you from the dentist...fear, embarrassment, anxiety, or any other medical condition...you don't need to live in pain. Dr. Smith can and will fix it because everyone deserves to smile<//Review>

<pictures>None<//pictures><time>1508106269516<//time>< Review>
I used to like this place. Not sure what changed. The staff was friendly, our server was nice and the environtment seemed chill and casual, but the food was not the best quality. The terikyaki beef tasted old, sort of like it had been recently unfrozen, and was cold. The sashimi did not taste fresh and was a little icey. The steamed rice was mushy. My partner's rice had something in it that wasn't rice (a small pink particle). Other than that, the miso soup was good. The crunchy roll was so sweet it hurt my stomach, but tasted good. Food-wise everything else was okay.</Review>

< Text>
5-18-21 @ 12:40 pm I went through the drop off at this Goodwill ElToro Rd. I pulled up and before you drive through you need to wear a mask and remain in your car. So when I got to the drop off area I rolled down my window and told the nice man to take the white bags in my trunk. He did and I drove off. When I got home I realized that one of the white bags was a purchase I just made. So I rushed back there and told a employee what I did. He was so sweet he started looking for my bag, then one other and I think the lady that helped was a manager.These 3 people went above and beyond to help me. They found my bag. I was so happy you have no idea..Just goes to show they‚Äôre a lot of wonderful people that are willing to help. I wish I had names.. Thank you!!<//Text>

< review>
This is probably one of the larger Goodwill‚Äôs in the area. This is the time to get your Halloween costumes on the cheap! See the photos attached. A good portion in the center of the store was dedicated just to Halloween costumes.

More than half the store is clothes.
There is an entire other store right next to this one called OC Goodwill Boutique which is mostly high end, designer clothing with some couture. See my other review for those photos.

Not as much furniture at this Goodwill. Mostly side tables and chairs.
A good amount of housewares, small counter top appliances, lamps, home decor, linen, toys and shoes can be found here.

Like most other stores at this time, the fitting rooms are closed and there are no public restrooms available.<//review>
<date>1601687332428<//date><gmap_id>0x80dce8f0721f1b51:0x48be0ac52e3f0f30<//gmap_id></record>

Carol Meldrum</name>

4< /rate>
< review>
I usually shop GW on Tuesdays to take advantage of the senior citizen discount. I have shopped here for years and have found several bargains.
I have noticed the increased prices. I realize that costs associated with having a storefront have increased and they have to factor several costs into their items for sale. I am fortunate enough to be able to afford the cost increase, but realize that there are many that are not so fortunate. It might help to post in the stores the days that clothing with a certain color tag will be 50% off. Not everyone can come in and check the signs everyday to see what is in sale.
I would also suggest that GW provide shoppers to help people with special needs. There must be volunteer groups that would be happy to help people that have sight, or mobility problems. Volunteers don't have to be paid emotes and can sign wavers for any perceived injuries that may happen.
Than you Goodwill for being a part of our community and providing your help and assistance to our community.< /review>
< Pics>
None<//Pics>

‚Ä¢

< Review>
Top notch local spot. It's ostensibly a teriyaki joint with all the standard varieties of bento boxes, soba dishes, and tempura. I would put their bento boxes up against any others in Sacramento and at a great value on top on that, but don't sleep on the Korean offerings! Their bibimbap is a 10/10 in my book. The locale isn't fancy, but the food is extremely high quality and consistently good.</Review>

<rating>5</rating>< Review>
I met with Dr. Tim Davis seeking help from chronic knee pain I have been experiencing since a total knee replacement in 2015.  My original surgeon told me I should lower my expectations.

I met with Dr. Davis in early February and he explained  a procedure that would block the nerve in my leg.  A few weeks later I had the outpatient procedure.  I was in and out in a few hours and felt immediate relief.

Dr. Davis and his entire staff are friendly, welcoming, caring and efficient.  My wait time has been under 15 minutes to see the doctors.

Dr. Davis is hands on and truly cares about his patients.  At the end of our appointment he always checks in to see if I'm satisfied with him and his front office.

I have already referred several people to Dr. Davis and will happily continue doing so.</Review>

<username>John Jackson-Pina</username>< text>
The term refreshing does not begin to describe my experience with this store. I have worked the customer service industry for years and lived by a code I so rarely encounter nowadays. Treat others with kindness, honesty, and respect. This is my way. In these last few years dealing with people while I'm out and about, so few have taken that to heart better than Mr. Alex Carrel.

What was supposed to be a simple inquiry of the site and its pricing turned into a worth while exchange that both answered the questions I asked and even some that I had no idea I should have even mentioned. I visited other sites of Extra Space before and only a handful even come close to the warm and friendly atmosphere offered by this one.

Mr. Carrel has proved quite patient and understanding when dealing with others and even the manager proved to be quite a treat to deal with. I take the time to write and recommend so few places to others online, but this one is an exception. If you are expecting a run of the mill box checking slog I'll tell you now you wont find it here. However, if your looking for a generally helpful staff with reasonable pricing, I can not offer more praise than this store.< /text>

<Name>Patrick Diola</Name><Date>1580164428629<//Date><rating>1<//rating><Text>Raised my rent on a 10x10 unit $100 in one shot with barely any notice. I'd be better off setting all my belongings on fire and buying new stuff when needed. I'm working on recycling, donating and selling everything and will be moving out as soon as I can.

EDIT: To respond to Extra Space's reply- I already did call and the local office said that "corporate" sets the rates and that they'll have "someone" call me to "talk" about it. I asked who that would be so that I could make the call to the right people and the answer was an ambiguous "someone" up the chain.

I won't change my review. This was a bait and switch. And, it turns out that Extra Space has had a class action lawsuit filed recently (Johnson et al. v. Extra Space Storage Inc.) alleging that ExtraSpace is using bait-and-switch to lure people in at lower rates and then jacking up the rent astronomically once they've spent weeks painstakingly moving everything into their storage units.

TL;DR ExtraSpace will jack up your rent 10%-50% about every 6 months. My most recent increase was 50% after not even 6 months. They are currently being sued for bait-and-switch. Do a google search for "Class Action Lawsuit Extra Space" to see what you'll be getting in to.< /Text>< Pictures>

< user>
116413415978657913876< /user>
<user_name>John B<//user_name><Date>1457141085349<//Date><rate>2< /rate>< text>
Be prepared for significant price increases just a few months after renting here.  Month-to-month seems like a renter-friendly policy until they raise prices (and we're not talking small increases) at the worst possible time (they know you're kind of locked-in if you have a large unit, even though it's a monthly contract).  I'm accustomed to small price increases after a year, but what they do is almost unethical (although not technically illegal).  They need to be more upfront about this, especially for an Alameda-based business.

Note: I used Extra Space in another city for almost three years, and I never once had this issue, so I'm not sure if I believe the "Decisions are made by corporate headquarters, it's out of our control" line.

They could also give their facilities a facelift, and not just their front entrance and main office (which are freshly painted for their website photos).  Hallways are damp (smell like mold), dark, and narrow, and the lightweight partitions seem like they can easily be broken into.  Not good considering their location is next to a lot of vacant warehouses and old industrial buildings on a poorly lit street.  Since I'm not storing anything of value, I can deal with dated facilities.  But I never feel comfortable going here alone at dark.</text>

0x808f86c1d7d0b2f1:0x2f33e1e61c623e72< /Gmap_id>
< review>
Be prepared for significant price increases just a few months after renting here.  Month-to-month seems like a renter-friendly policy until they raise prices (and we're not talking small increases) at the worst possible time (they know you're kind of locked-in if you have a large unit, even though it's a monthly contract).  I'm accustomed to small price increases after a year, but what they do is almost unethical (although not technically illegal).  They need to be more upfront about this, especially for an Alameda-based business.

Note: I used Extra Space in another city for almost three years, and I never once had this issue, so I'm not sure if I believe the "Decisions are made by corporate headquarters, it's out of our control" line.

They could also give their facilities a facelift, and not just their front entrance and main office (which are freshly painted for their website photos).  Hallways are damp (smell like mold), dark, and narrow, and the lightweight partitions seem like they can easily be broken into.  Not good considering their location is next to a lot of vacant warehouses and old industrial buildings on a poorly lit street.  Since I'm not storing anything of value, I can deal with dated facilities.  But I never feel comfortable going here alone at dark.</review>

2</rate>
